{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Lemon sabayon sauce","content":["Place Parmesan cheese in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place water and vegetable stock paste in mixing bowl, insert simmering basket and add basmati rice to it.","If ends of asparagus are woody, snap or cut them off, or peel lower third of stems if preferred. Arrange asparagus in Varoma dish, stacking each layer in alternate directions to allow steam to circulate. Set Varoma in position and steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma and remove simmering basket using spatula, transfer rice to a serving plate, drizzle with extra virgin olive oil, cover and set aside. Check whether asparagus is cooked. If not, set Varoma back in position and steam a further <nobr>5-10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep asparagus warm. Set scale to zero and transfer 120 g cooking liquid to a small bowl (scale will show ‘-120 g’ when mixing bowl is set back in position), discarding the rest. Set small bowl aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces","1200 g water","1 tsp vegetable stock paste, homemade","200 g basmati rice","500 - 700 g green asparagus","40 g extra virgin olive oil"]},{"title":"Lemon sabayon sauce","content":["4 egg yolks","½ tsp salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","10 g lemon juice, freshly squeezed"]}],"id":"r80514","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-EQKsk2UnJxw\/XZVRbnelG9I\/AAAAAAAAdOU\/u-7gycnPEt0FrxHJhBtSGmOwv12I_J7xQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_oA0MuwU8BN-cl8Tn.png","title":"Asparagus, Parmesan rice and lemon sabayon sauce","publishedAt":"2017-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"20 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"41 g","calories":"1685 kJ \/ 403 kcal"},"usefulItems":"vegetable peeler","hintsAndTricks":["The luscious lemon sabayon sauce for this vegetarian dish is almost as luxurious as hollandaise, without all the butter. If you prefer potatoes to rice, use the same cooking method, just make sure to check the cooking times on both the asparagus and the potatoes, removing whichever one is cooked through before the other.","If using white asparagus, in <nobr>step 3<\/nobr> steam a further <nobr><strong>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong><\/nobr> after removing simmering basket with rice."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","4 portions"]}